  "text": "The access control and row-level security implementation spans several layers: (1) **IAccessStorage** hierarchy: base interface `IAccessStorage` with implementations `DiskAccessStorage`, `UsersConfigAccessStorage`, `ReplicatedAccessStorage`, `MemoryAccessStorage`, `LDAPAccessStorage`, and `MultipleAccessStorage` (composite). (2) **AccessControl** extends `MultipleAccessStorage` as the top-level manager, holding caches for roles, row policies, quotas, and settings profiles, and providing `ContextAccess` instances per-query. (3) **ContextAccess** checks permissions using `AccessRights`, `EnabledRoles`, and `EnabledRowPolicies`. `CachedAccessChecking` wraps it for repeated checks. (4) **Row-level security**: `RowPolicy` entity \u2192 `RowPolicyCache` watches storage \u2192 `EnabledRowPolicies` generates `RowPolicyFilter` AST nodes attached to queries. `RowPolicyDefs` defines filter types (SELECT, INSERT, etc.). (5) **User/Role resolution**: `User` and `Role` entities, `GrantedRoles` tracks granted roles, `RolesOrUsersSet` for wildcard matching, `RoleCache`/`EnabledRoles`/`EnabledRolesInfo` for role graph resolution. (6) **GRANT/REVOKE**: `ParserGrantQuery` \u2192 `ASTGrantQuery` \u2192 `InterpreterGrantQuery` (handles both GRANT and REVOKE).",
